<TITLE> Sylhet's rail link with Dhaka, Ctg back on track </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Moulvibazar, June 29 (bdnews24.com) Sylhet's rail links with Dhaka and Chittagong were restored Friday after remaining snapped for nine hours. Sylhet-Dhaka and Sylhet-Chittagong rail communications went off the track after a train collided with a truck at Teliapara level crossing in Habiganj early Friday. Abdul Aziz, assistant station- master of Srimangal railway station, said a relief train from Akhaura junction started rescue operations early Friday. Train communications became normal after Friday noon, he added. Aziz said following the collision between the Sylhet-bound Surma Mail and a goods- laden truck at about 3am the engine of the train jumped the rails. Surma Mail driver Abdul Aziz and assistant driver Saidul Haque were seriously injured in the incident. They were first admitted into Habiganj Sadar Hospital before being moved to National Orthopaedic Hospital in Dhaka, the station master said. Parabat Express, Joyontika Express and Kushiara Express stranded at different stations headed for their destinations after the links were restored. bdnews24.com/cor
